webdriver_test_tools.project.initialize.create_file_from_template(template_path, target_path, filename, context)[source]¶

Short hand function that renders a template with the specified filename followed by a ‘.j2’ extension from the template path to a file with the specified name in the target path

The use of ‘.j2’ as a file extension is to distinguish templates from package modules.

Parameters:
  • template_path – Path to template directory
  • target_path – Path to target directory
  • filename – Name of the template file. Will be used as the filename for the

rendered file written to the target directory :param context: Jinja context used to render template
